Since I‚Äôve been doing yoga I‚Äôve noticed that my anxiety has actually lessened a bit. I‚Äôm able to tackle assignments and online schooling with a calmer mindset? Idk. I used to get easily overwhelmed (ADHD) and get panic attacks, but creating a routine of waking up at 7:30 a.m. to do yoga has improved my ability to tackle the day. 

I run as well as do strength training. I used to think these exercises alone would supply me with enough endorphins but no matter how much I ran I still felt anxious. Adding yoga to my life has been one of the best decisions I‚Äôve ever made. 

Yoga made me LISTEN to my body. Instead of tiring it out, I‚Äôve now been paying attention to how yoga energizes my body and mind while calming the relationship between the two. I‚Äôm stronger now in all the microscopic ways that running and strength training overlooked. 

So while strength training makes me a better runner, yoga has made me a better athlete (and student) overall.

I can't believe I made it this far! this is the first time I did something for my health,, I tried jogging but only lasted 3 consecutive days, then I quit, and never again did some exercise,, until I started this 30 days yoga challenge! I started this because I feel dizzy one day,, I thought it will pass, but after 3 days, all the symptoms points to vertigo. my aunt has vertigo so I pretty much know about it, I'm afraid that it's because of my ear, I had a small wound inside coz I'm careless, or maybe because of lack of sleep, I don't know, (I'm afraid to go to the doctor) so anyway,, I noticed that I'm loosing my balance,, but I can still walk, but it's not the same as before, I don't feel my normal self. I'm not dizzy all the time, just when I'm walking or standing. Still, I don't feel normal. My aunt had rehab to regain her balance,, since she lost her balance when she had her first episode of vertigo, it was really bad. So, I was afraid,, I didn't tell my family what I'm experiencing , I started copying my aunt's exercises that she learned from her physical therapist. Then I started this yoga challenge, at first week, I have two consecutive days that I didn't feel dizzy,, as of today,, I didn't feel dizzy for about a week now, I'll continue doing this even of I'm not dizzy anymore,, Thanks for this, Adriene!
